content.description: Crux at midpoint. Fun Ride.  lots of loose dirt and rocks at the base of this climb and on the way to the upper wall. Route is in a nice shaded area in the afternoon with a good photo ops from the base of the upper wall.
content.protection: Sport, Rap rings at the top
content.location: Start at the tree in the gulley on the way up to the upper wall on the right side of the crag.

content.description: watch out for scorpions close to the top.
content.location: on it's own section of rock between the upper and lower walls. Rap rings at the top with a nice ledge to stand on.

content.description: Another good beginer route. Crux is in the thin section just below the first ledge.
content.location: Right side of the lower wall. Shared Anchors with Fried Chicken, and Creature Feature.

content.protection: Sport. This route ends at a set of rap rings that are the anchors for all of the routes on the lower wall at Devil's Rejects.
content.location: Start just to the right of the tree on the west facing part of the wall. Climb straight up and stay left of the large feature close to the top.

content.description: Longest route at Devil's Rejects. Good first lead or beginer route.
content.location: Route closest to the road and lowest on the hill.  Shared rap rings at the top.

content.description: fun pumpy 5.8   good place to top belay, take pictures, or teach cleaning a route.
content.protection: Sport. Shares rap ring anchors with Captain Spaulding at a very nice ledge.
content.location: Left route on the upper wall. scramble up past tree and  "murder ride" watch out for loose rock and dirt.

content.protection: sport, shares anchor rings with Dr. Satan
content.location: right route on the upper wall area.

content.description: This is a mostly south & east facing cliff just a few minutes hike from the US 60.  Fried Chicken and Gasoline is a west facing route.  There is shade on most of the routes in the afternoon.   The rock is typical to the Queen Creek area. The area is mostly sport with one crack that can be top roped.
